CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1958, pg. 1 reads: "Breakfast At The Pooles - Mr. and Mrs. W.T. Poole entertained several members of the United Supreme Council 33 decree Scottish Rite Masons, PHM, during their stay in Pittsburgh. in left photo, left to right, are Mrs. Edward Robinson, Dr. Edward Robinson, Atty. Joseph W. Givens, Pittsburgh member of the Supreme Council; Mrs. William Cuthbert, Mrs. Marian Bryant.  Standing: Mr. Poole, Supreme Council member and Grand Minister of State; Mrs. Joseph Givens, Leland French, Cleveland (Ohio) member; Dr. A.P. Knott, Mrs. Homer S. Brown, Dr. William Cuthbert, Mrs. William A. Heathman Providence, R.I.; Frank E. Bolden and Judge Homer S. Brown...Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: United Supreme Council 33 degree Scottish Rite Masons and guests from left: Mrs. Edward Robinson, Dr. Edward Robinson, Atty. Joseph W. Givens, Mrs. William Cuthbert, Marian Bryant,  W. T. Poole, Mrs. Joseph Givens, Leland French, Dr. A. P. Knott, Wilhelmina Brown, Dr. William Cuthbert, Mrs. William A. Heathman, Frank E. Bolden, and Judge Homer S. Brown, gathered around table in Poole home
